spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:script:
Enable('USE_SOFT_FIFO', Or(Eq('RX_FIFO', 'Enable RX FIFO'), Eq('TX_FIFO', 'Enable TX FIFO')));\ Enable('BAUD_VALUE', Eq('FIXEDMODE', 'Fixed'));\ Enable('PRG_BIT8', Eq('FIXEDMODE', 'Fixed'));\ Enable('PRG_PARITY', Eq('FIXEDMODE', 'Fixed'));\ Enable('BAUD_VAL_FRCTN', And(Eq('FIXEDMODE', 'Fixed'), Eq('BAUD_VAL_FRCTN_EN', '1')));\ Tooltip('BAUD_VAL_FRCTN', 'This setting is only relevant when Configuration is set to Fixed and the Enable Extra Precision option has been checked.
The value chosen here is added to the baud value set above to give a precise baud value.');\ Tooltip('BAUD_VAL_FRCTN_EN', 'When Configuration is set to Programmable, checking this option enables an additional control register that can be used to set a fractional part for the baud value. The baud value can be set with a precision of 0.125.
When Configuration is set to Fixed, checking this option allows you to set a fixed fractional part for the baud value. The size of the fractional part is specified in the next setting.');\

spirit:vendorExtensions.actel-cc:description: CoreUARTapb is a serial communication controller with a flexible serial data interface that is intended primarily for embedded systems. The controller operates as an asynchronous (UART) with a control register interface and APB wrapper.
